NAME

      gcloud preview autoscaler update - update Autoscaler instances

SYNOPSIS

      gcloud preview autoscaler update NAME
         [--cool-down-period COOL_DOWN_PERIOD] [--custom-metric CUSTOM_METRIC]
         [--custom-metric-utilization-target-type CUSTOM_METRIC_UTILIZATION_TARGET_TYPE]
         [--description DESCRIPTION] [--format FORMAT] [--help]
         [--max-num-replicas MAX_NUM_REPLICAS]
         [--min-num-replicas MIN_NUM_REPLICAS] [--project PROJECT] [--quiet, -q]
         [--target TARGET] [--target-cpu-utilization TARGET_CPU_UTILIZATION]
         [--target-custom-metric-utilization TARGET_CUSTOM_METRIC_UTILIZATION]
         [--target-load-balancer-utilization TARGET_LOAD_BALANCER_UTILIZATION]
         [-h]

DESCRIPTION

      Update Autoscaler instances.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS

      NAME

         Autoscaler name.

FLAGS

      --cool-down-period COOL_DOWN_PERIOD

         Number of seconds Autoscaler will wait between resizing collection.

      --custom-metric CUSTOM_METRIC

         A Google Cloud Monitoring instance metric (see
         https://developers.google.com/cloud-monitoring/metrics).

      --custom-metric-utilization-target-type
         CUSTOM_METRIC_UTILIZATION_TARGET_TYPE

         Type of target you specified, you can choose from the following: GAUGE,
         DELTA_PER_SECOND, DELTA_PER_MINUTE.

      --description DESCRIPTION

         Notes about Autoscaler.

      --max-num-replicas MAX_NUM_REPLICAS

         Maximum number of replicas Autoscaler will set.

      --min-num-replicas MIN_NUM_REPLICAS

         Minimum number of replicas Autoscaler will set.

      --target TARGET

         Resource to be scaled.

      --target-cpu-utilization TARGET_CPU_UTILIZATION

         CPU utilization level Autoscaler will aim to maintain (0.0 to 1.0).

      --target-custom-metric-utilization TARGET_CUSTOM_METRIC_UTILIZATION

         Custom metric level Autoscaler will aim to maintain (greater than 0.0).

      --target-load-balancer-utilization TARGET_LOAD_BALANCER_UTILIZATION

         Load balancer utilization level Autoscaler will aim to maintain
         (greater than 0.0).

GLOBAL FLAGS

      --format FORMAT

         Specify a format for printed output. By default, a command-specific
         human-friendly output format is used. Setting this flag to one of the
         available options will serialize the result of the command in the
         chosen format and print it to stdout. Supported formats are: json,
         text, yaml.

      --help

         Display detailed help.

      --project PROJECT

         The Google Cloud Platform project name to use for this invocation. If
         omitted then the current project is assumed.

      --quiet, -q

         Disable all interactive prompts when running gcloud commands. If input
         is required, defaults will be used, or an error will be raised.

      -h

         Print a summary help and exit.

NOTES

      This command is in the Google Cloud SDK preview component. See installing
      components if it is not installed.

